### 2. Phase 4: Voice & Accessibility MVP 

The MVP requirement involves adding the Web Speech API securely onto our Clerk application state, and pointing it towards the `POST /v1/voice/agent` router you created via Claude integration.

#### [MODIFY] [store/useAppStore.ts](file:///c:/PaperTrail_Colohacks/frontend/src/store/useAppStore.ts)
- Extend `UserProfile` to support `preferred_language`, `voice_mode_enabled`, and `voice_agent_enabled`.

#### [MODIFY] [(auth)/signup/page.tsx](file:///c:/PaperTrail_Colohacks/frontend/src/app/(auth)/signup/page.tsx)
- Embed a dropdown to select the `preferred_language` on Registration (e.g. English `en-IN`, Hindi `hi-IN`). Pass this dynamically with `POST /v1/auth/register`.

#### [MODIFY] [(clerk)/settings/page.tsx](file:///c:/PaperTrail_Colohacks/frontend/src/app/(clerk)/settings/page.tsx) (Assuming existence or will add to Layout)
- We will construct the UI for Clerks to patch their configurations to `PATCH /v1/users/me/preferences`.

#### [MODIFY] [(clerk)/upload/review/page.tsx](file:///c:/PaperTrail_Colohacks/frontend/src/app/(clerk)/upload/review/page.tsx)
- **TTS**: If `voice_mode_enabled` is active, we trigger `window.speechSynthesis` natively telling the user how many low-confidence fields require their checking.
- **STT**: Display a Microphone UI on screen if `voice_agent_enabled`. Uses HTML `SpeechRecognition` translating spoken words up to `POST /v1/voice/agent` alongside our `extracted_fields`. It will play audio of the Claude-responded guidance in the set language and flash bounding boxes matching `field_referenced`!

